ava library for tests that provides lightweight, throwaway instances of databases, web browsers, and other services running in Docker containers. It helps integration tests run against real dependencies instead of mocks or in-memory substitutes.\",\nmetadata/org.testcontainers/junit-jupiter/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Testcontainers JUnit Jupiter provides a JUnit 5 extension for managing Testcontainers-managed Docker containers during tests. It supplies the @Testcontainers and @Container annotations so containers can be started and stopped per test method or shared across a test class.\",\nmetadata/org.testcontainers/testcontainers/1.17.6/reachability-metadata.json:7:      \"type\": \"com.github.dockerjava.api.command.AsyncDockerCmd\"\nmetadata/org.testcontainers/testcontainers/1.17.6/reachability-metadata.json:11:        \"typeReached\": \"org.testcontainers.DockerClientFactory\"\nmetadata/org.testcontainers/testcontainers/1.17.6/reachability-metadata.json:19:        \"typeReached\": \"org.testcontainers.DockerClientFactory\"\nmetadata/org.testcontainers/testcontainers/1.17.6/reachability-metadata.json:51:        \"typeReached\": \"org.testcontainers.DockerClientFactory\"\nmetadata/org.testcontainers/testcontainers/1.17.6/reachability-metadata.json:59:        \"typeReached\": \"org.testcontainers.DockerClientFactory\"\nmetadata/org.testcontainers/testcontainers/1.17.6/reachability-metadata.json:67:        \"typeReached\": \"org.testcontainers.DockerClientFactory\"\nmetadata/org.testcontainers/testcontainers/1.17.6/reachability-metadata.json:75:        \"typeReached\": \"org.testcontainers.DockerClientFactory\"\nmetadata/org.testcontainers/testcontainers/1.17.6/reachability-metadata.json:83:        \"typeReached\": \"org.testcontainers.DockerClientFactory\"\nmetadata/org.testcontainers/testcontainers/1.17.6/reachability-metadata.json:93:      \"type\": \"com.github.dockerjava.api.command.DockerCmd\"\nmetadata/org.testcontainers/testcontainers/1.17.6/reachab